summary:
As a serial entrepreneur, Robbert Jan enjoys developing disruptive data companies for stodgy old industries. Robbert Jan has hands-on experience in corporate sales, fundraising, and venture capital & private equity deal-making.

As the architect behind Holland Startup, he now fulfills his personal ambition: "enable aspiring entrepreneurs to reach their highest potential and purpose in life". Since its inception in 2014, Robbert Jan worked with 50+ entrepreneurs to start 19 startups, and raised EUR10m+ in venture funding from individual investors, governments and family offices.

On his way to Holland Startup, Robbert Jan co-founded two companies Spotney.com (2012) a big data company that helped brands like Zalando and Wehkamp sell more online, and E2Ma (2002) a leader in Online Lead Generation, active in 5 European countries, employing 40+ people, serving over 1.000 customers.

His career began (1998) in the online media & gaming industry where he was "first-hire" of online gaming company Gamegate.com, before discovering his calling as an internet entrepreneur. As to educational background, Robbert Jan graduated from HZ University of Applied Sciences and holds a bachelor's degree in business engineering.
